\begin_layout Subsection
How does BN help optimization?
 (15%)
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:How-does-BN"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not enough to just use BN.
 We should understand why it can play a positive role in our optimization process so as to have a more comprehensive understanding of the optimization process of deep learning and select the appropriate network structure according to the actual situation in the future works.
 You may want to check some papers,
 e.g.,
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "bn-paper"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So what stands behind BN?
 After all,
 in order to understand how BN affects the training performance it would be logical to examine the effect that BN has on the corresponding optimization landscape.
 To this end,
 recall that our training is performed using gradient descent method and this method draws on the first-order optimization paradigm.
 In this paradigm,
 we use the local linear approximation of the loss around the current solution to identify the best update step to take.
 Consequently,
 the performance of these algorithms is largely determined by how predictive of the nearby loss landscape this local approximation is.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Recent research results show that 
\emph on
BN reparametrizes the underlying optimization problem to make its landscape significantly more smooth
\emph default
.
 So along this line,
 we are going to measure:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Loss landscape or variation of the value of the loss;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Gradient predictiveness or the change of the loss gradient;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Maximum difference in gradient over the distance.
\end_layout

